properties.sfomuseum:description: Brochure and letter issued by TWA (Trans World Airlines) promoting the airline’s Boeing 707 fleet;a. brochure; multipage booklet; blue cover with color illustration of Boeing 707 in flight and text “The world’s fastest and largest jetliner”;b. introduction letter; single sheet; typewritten letter dated November 12, 1959 from Louis P. Marechal, Vice President and General Sales Manager describing 707 service; includes handwritten note from “Stan”: “May I have it after it’s been ‘the rounds’?”
